{#
  hx-button — Drupal Twig Template
  ==================================

  Server-renders the hx-button custom element with correct attributes.
  JavaScript enhancement (hx-click events, form submission) is handled automatically
  by the component — no Drupal behavior is required for standard usage.

  Note on hx-size: The size attribute is intentionally prefixed as `hx-size` rather than
  `size` to avoid conflicts with the native HTML `size` attribute on form elements. This
  diverges from HTML naming conventions and will be normalized to `size` in a future major
  version. Until then, use `hx-size` when setting size from Twig templates.

  Note on htmx: If your project uses htmx, be aware that `hx-*` attribute names are
  reserved by htmx. The `hx-size` attribute used by this component does not conflict
  with any htmx attributes, but avoid adding other `hx-*` attributes that htmx may
  interpret as directives.

  Parameters:
    label      (string)  Required for text buttons. Visible button label text.
    variant    (string)  Optional. One of: primary | secondary | tertiary | danger | ghost | outline.
                         Defaults to 'primary'.
    size       (string)  Optional. One of: sm | md | lg. Defaults to 'md'.
                         Rendered as the `hx-size` attribute on the element.
    disabled   (bool)    Optional. Renders the button in a disabled, non-interactive state.
    loading    (bool)    Optional. Renders the button with a spinner and prevents interaction.
    type       (string)  Optional. One of: button | submit | reset. Defaults to 'button'.
                         Ignored when href is set.
    href       (string)  Optional. When set, renders an anchor element instead of a button.
    target     (string)  Optional. Anchor target. Only used when href is set.
                         Use '_blank' to open in a new tab (rel="noopener noreferrer" is
                         automatically applied by the component for security).
    name       (string)  Optional. Form field name for ElementInternals form submission.
    value      (string)  Optional. Form field value submitted with name on form submission.
    aria_label (string)  Optional. Forwarded to the inner button/anchor element. Required
                         for icon-only buttons where no visible label text is present.
    attributes (object)  Optional. Additional HTML attributes to spread onto the element.

  Slots (Twig blocks):
    prefix — Content rendered before the label (icons, SVG).
    default — The button label (set via `label` parameter or override this block).
    suffix — Content rendered after the label (icons, trailing chevrons).

  Usage examples:

    Primary action button:
      {% include 'hx-button.twig' with {
        label: 'Save Patient Record',
        variant: 'primary',
        type: 'submit',
      } %}

    Destructive action button:
      {% include 'hx-button.twig' with {
        label: 'Discharge Patient',
        variant: 'danger',
        size: 'sm',
      } %}

    Link button (opens in new tab):
      {% include 'hx-button.twig' with {
        label: 'View Lab Results',
        variant: 'ghost',
        href: node.field_lab_results_url.value,
        target: '_blank',
      } %}

    Icon-only button (accessible name required):
      {% include 'hx-button.twig' with {
        variant: 'ghost',
        aria_label: 'Close dialog',
      } %}

    Loading state (form submission in progress):
      {% include 'hx-button.twig' with {
        label: 'Submitting...',
        loading: true,
        disabled: true,
      } %}

  Drupal behavior for dynamic interactions:
    The component dispatches an `hx-click` CustomEvent (bubbles, composed) on activation.
    For standard form submission, set `type="submit"` — no Drupal behavior required.
    For AJAX-driven patterns, attach a behavior to listen for `hx-click`:

      (function (Drupal, once) {
        Drupal.behaviors.helixButton = {
          attach: function (context) {
            once('hx-button-ajax', 'hx-button[data-ajax-action]', context).forEach((btn) => {
              btn.addEventListener('hx-click', (e) => {
                const action = btn.dataset.ajaxAction;
                Drupal.ajax({ url: action }).execute();
              });
            });
          },
        };
      })(Drupal, once);
#}

<hx-button
  variant="{{ variant|default('primary') }}"
  hx-size="{{ size|default('md') }}"
  {% if disabled %}disabled{% endif %}
  {% if loading %}loading{% endif %}
  {% if type is defined and not href %}type="{{ type }}"{% endif %}
  {% if href %}href="{{ href }}"{% endif %}
  {% if target %}target="{{ target }}"{% endif %}
  {% if name %}name="{{ name }}"{% endif %}
  {% if value %}value="{{ value }}"{% endif %}
  {% if aria_label %}aria-label="{{ aria_label }}"{% endif %}
  {% for key, val in attributes|default({}) %}{{ key }}="{{ val }}" {% endfor %}
>
  {%- set prefix_content %}{% block prefix %}{% endblock %}{% endset -%}
  {%- if prefix_content %}<span slot="prefix">{{ prefix_content }}</span>{% endif -%}
  {%- block default %}{%- if label %}{{ label }}{% endif -%}{% endblock -%}
  {%- set suffix_content %}{% block suffix %}{% endblock %}{% endset -%}
  {%- if suffix_content %}<span slot="suffix">{{ suffix_content }}</span>{% endif -%}
</hx-button>
